  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      After the child birth most women experience major health issues such as depression, severe
      fatigue, back pain, perineal pain, mastitis, urinary or faecal incontinence, sexual problems
      and relationship problems with partners. That all lead to poorer emotional and mental health
      and factors contributing isolation, exhaustion and physical health problems.

      'Sava Mahina (6-week period) is a traditional practice for postpartum women in India, which
      include special diet, lifestyle and supportive care. The current multicenter randomized
      controlled trial (RCT) aims to evaluate outcomes of Indian postpartum care on women.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
